   Total Drug Abuse Violation Arrests 7,717 35,202 Drugs10 ÿ Cocaine and
   Crack Powder and crack cocaine continue to be available throughout the
   region. Large quantities of cocaine are coming from sources in the New
   York City area by private automobiles and by couriers using bus and
   rail transportation. ÿ Heroin High purity and inexpensive heroin is
   readily available in many areas of the W/B HIDTA region. It is
   generally of the South American variety and comes from New York City.
   Law enforcement agencies in both Baltimore City and Washington, D.C.
   report that the availability of heroin is high in their areas. ÿ
   Marijuana Marijuana is readily available throughout this region and its
   use continues to rise, especially among juveniles. Most of the
   marijuana found here is coming from the southwest area of the country
   and much can be linked to commercial parcel services. ÿ Other Drugs LSD
   is still readily accessible in the W/B metropolitan area either via
   local rave parties or independent dealers in the suburban areas. The
   distribution and abuse of methamphetamine are increasing throughout
   this region. Police in suburban Maryland describe a variety of drugs
   related to rave parties including MDMA, LSD and LSD lookalikes,
   ketamine, and various legal and illegal drugs used in combination.
   Juveniles11 ÿ In a Statewide survey conducted in April 2001, 16.9% of
   Maryland 8th graders reported that they had used marijuana at least
   once during their lifetime. ÿ 5% of 6th graders reported using
   inhalants at least once during their lifetime. ONDCP Clearinghouse 4
