   2000, $541,793 in assets was seized by the Drug Enforcement Command of
   the Maryland State Police through their Marijuana Eradication
   Program.12 Results of Maryland's Marijuana Eradication Program, 1998-99
   Plants Seized Plots Located Arrests Made Assets Seized 1998 3,475 151
   84 $507,366 1999 3,610 267 143 $1,087,181 2000 6,954 298 109 $541,793 ÿ
   During 1999, Federal and State/local authorities in Maryland seized one
   methamphetamine laboratory. There were no clandestine laboratory
   seizures reported to the El Paso Intelligence Center for 2000 or
   January to July of 2001.13 Consequences of Use ÿ During 2000, the State
   medical examiner's office reported 474 heroin-related overdoses
   throughout the State. 304 of these overdoses occurred in Baltimore.14 ÿ
   Heroin was mentioned in 81.0% of the drug abuse deaths reported by
   Medical Examiners (ME) in Baltimore during 1999.15 Estimated Number of
