   and Drug Abuse Administration (ADAA):28 * Intermediate Care Facility
   (ICF): a residential treatment facility for alcohol and drug clients
   who do not require hospitalization. * Chemotherapeutic: a
   non-residential program offering treatment and rehabilitation employing
   methadone in the detoxification or maintenance treatment of opiate and
   narcotic drug abusers. * Correctional Treatment Services: alcohol and
   drug abuse assessment, treatment, and rehabilitation services delivered
